The paper deals with the problem of probability calibration for models that produce class probability estimates from sequences of data. This makes it likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and cryptography and security (cs.CR) as these sub-categories often deal with sequential data and modeling.
